name: Mike Nouveau
bio:
Vintage Watch Specialist
TikTok is my main platform. I post here if I remember.
No authentication or consultation via DMs. 
👇🏼 Better content here👇🏼

social_posts.post_text: I swapped the Cristallor I found in Tokyo for one with a little extra sauce. Cartier logo at 6 o’clock to make way for the Bahraini emblem at 12. How many of these can possibly be floating around?
Sat down with my friend @je_tomm to talk about my little vintage watch collection. Shot by @chrisc0e for @chrono24. See the full video on Chrono24’s YouTube page.

A stunning 1960 Boucheron Reflet with clous de Paris case, dial, and matching brick bracelet. Hand engravings indicating an Ω Omega movement, a patented (in 1944!) quick-release bracelet, and a ridiculous amount of hallmarks… including one stamped directly into the side of the hobnail case. Shockingly undervalued (for now). NFS.
